1
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,800
What is this, Mr. Kobayashi?

2
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,170
Shouldn't I

3
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:35,280
=Cases Between Us=
be asking you that, Chief Yuan?

4
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:38,039
=Episode 30=
You snuck into my banquet the other day,

5
00:00:38,040 --> 00:00:40,640
and now my gambling house.

6
00:00:40,890 --> 00:00:42,570
Chief Yuan,

7
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:45,279
why do you always show up uninvited?

8
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,490
Cut the crap.

9
00:00:46,570 --> 00:00:48,529
If you weren't up to no good,
I wouldn't be here.

10
00:00:48,530 --> 00:00:49,569
Where's Ma Buyan?

11
00:00:49,570 --> 00:00:51,040
You want him back?

12
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:52,359
What have you done to him?

13
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:53,359
Don't worry.

14
00:00:53,360 --> 00:00:55,569
He owes me money.

15
00:00:55,570 --> 00:00:57,320
He won't die yet.

16
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,639
How about this?

17
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:02,039
Chief Yuan is one of us.

18
00:01:02,040 --> 00:01:03,490
Since you're here,

19
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:05,370
let's settle it by the house rules.

20
00:01:05,770 --> 00:01:07,569
The wager is 1,000 silver coins.

21
00:01:07,570 --> 00:01:09,049
If you win,

22
00:01:09,050 --> 00:01:11,450
you can take him.

23
00:01:11,570 --> 00:01:12,730
Deal?

24
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,480
Put the guns down.

25
00:01:23,770 --> 00:01:25,560
You know how to gamble?

26
00:01:25,610 --> 00:01:26,279
Don't worry.

27
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,730
I used to play in school.

28
00:01:28,490 --> 00:01:30,170
I'll cover the 1,000 silver coins.

29
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,090
Once.

30
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:03,279
Chief Yuan,

31
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,530
after you.

32
00:02:38,930 --> 00:02:40,160
Call.

33
00:02:49,290 --> 00:02:50,680
Full house.

34
00:02:53,050 --> 00:02:53,769
Deal.

35
00:02:53,770 --> 00:02:56,030
(Lose)

36
00:03:06,110 --> 00:03:08,470
(Lose)

37
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:15,190
(Lose)

38
00:03:31,790 --> 00:03:35,510
(Lose)

39
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:45,610
Chief Yuan,

40
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:49,770
how about one hand to settle it all?

41
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:17,290
Deal.

42
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,359
You said you've only played once.

43
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,969
It was a fluke.

44
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:42,929
- I really did only play once.
- Not bad.

45
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:43,649
You're too slow.

46
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:45,000
I'm in a hurry to get him back.

47
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,529
I'll pay back.

48
00:05:47,530 --> 00:05:48,520
Stop!

49
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:49,970
I'll pay back.

50
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:52,849
Did we agree we'd get him if we won?

51
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:54,080
What are you doing?

52
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,440
You can have him.

53
00:05:58,060 --> 00:06:00,390
But he has to pay his debt.

54
00:06:00,550 --> 00:06:02,999
He said he couldn't pay,
so he volunteered to lose a hand instead.

55
00:06:02,999 --> 00:06:04,529
Does that look voluntary to you?

56
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:06,080
I...

57
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:07,929
I changed my mind.

58
00:06:07,930 --> 00:06:09,610
I'll pay back.

59
00:06:10,090 --> 00:06:11,320
What time did he get here?

60
00:06:11,670 --> 00:06:13,130
Around eight.

61
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,970
He gambled until dawn.

62
00:06:18,930 --> 00:06:20,490
How much does he owe? I'll pay it.

63
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,120
I have one condition.

64
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,679
Can I have the jade pendant

65
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:32,649
he pawned?

66
00:06:32,650 --> 00:06:33,880
Sure.

67
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,810
But it's a fake.

68
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,410
Fake?

69
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,200
Mr. Zhao,

70
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:45,760
they must've switched it

71
00:06:45,930 --> 00:06:47,559
to scam me.

72
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,609
Mr. Ma,

73
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:50,200
I beg to differ.

74
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:52,529
You couldn't repay your debt,

75
00:06:52,530 --> 00:06:54,239
so you pawned this jade pendant.

76
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,290
Right?

77
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:58,089
I only took it

78
00:06:58,090 --> 00:06:59,879
because I felt sorry for you.

79
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:02,200
The jade was nourished with
the blood of the dead.

80
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,810
Bad luck.

81
00:07:04,410 --> 00:07:06,520
I'm very superstitious.

82
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,320
You believe that?

83
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,239
Of course.

84
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,759
I wear red socks in my zodiac year,

85
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,879
carry a jade Pixiu,

86
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:18,560
and my license plate is triple eights.
(*Number 8 considered lucky)

87
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,000
I'm doing business in China,

88
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:25,560
so I'd better learn
how to court good fortune.

89
00:07:25,650 --> 00:07:27,200
You understand?

90
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,999
Who told you about
the blood of the dead?

91
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,199
An antique dealer

92
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,119
in Liulichang Antique Market told me.

93
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,849
When someone was buried,

94
00:07:34,850 --> 00:07:36,169
they'd stuff a white jade piece

95
00:07:36,170 --> 00:07:38,049
down the corpse's throat.

96
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:41,409
After centuries soaking
in rotting flesh and blood,

97
00:07:41,410 --> 00:07:42,610
they'd dig it up again,

98
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,520
and it'd become blood jade.

99
00:07:45,650 --> 00:07:46,880
Cut that out.

100
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,649
That's just the nonsense

101
00:07:48,650 --> 00:07:50,050
Zhang Baochen and the rest made up.

102
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,529
Real blood jade

103
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:53,529
gets its color from cinnabar
used in burial

104
00:07:53,530 --> 00:07:54,529
or from lying next

105
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,729
to iron objects.

106
00:07:55,730 --> 00:07:57,199
Most are purplish-red

107
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,049
or reddish-brown.

108
00:07:58,050 --> 00:07:59,239
After so many years,

109
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,849
the jade naturally weathers,

110
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:03,119
and the color seeps deep inside.

111
00:08:03,120 --> 00:08:04,729
This piece is only stained
on the surface,

112
00:08:04,730 --> 00:08:06,290
and the color's too faint.

113
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:10,370
It's sheep jade.

114
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:11,930
Sheep jade?

115
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,289
What is that?

116
00:08:13,290 --> 00:08:15,049
There are several ways
to replicate blood jade.

117
00:08:15,050 --> 00:08:17,169
Stain it with hawthorn,
soak it in pig's blood,

118
00:08:17,170 --> 00:08:18,529
or use a live animal.

119
00:08:18,530 --> 00:08:19,489
Oxen are too valuable,

120
00:08:19,490 --> 00:08:20,729
and dogs bite,

121
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:21,999
so most people use sheep.

122
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,529
They cut open its belly

123
00:08:23,530 --> 00:08:24,609
and place the jade inside.

124
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:25,409
Every time

125
00:08:25,410 --> 00:08:28,169
the sheep moves, it bleeds.

126
00:08:28,170 --> 00:08:31,760
Feed the jade with fresh blood
for a few years, then take it back out.

127
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,000
Now that's bad luck.

128
00:08:36,560 --> 00:08:38,760
You really know your stuff.

129
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,249
I grew up surrounded by antiques.

130
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:41,640
What do you think?

131
00:08:42,770 --> 00:08:46,250
You two are quite interesting.

132
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:53,289
(Jingshi Police Department)

133
00:08:53,290 --> 00:08:54,730
Yuzhen!

134
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,280
My dear sister!

135
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:02,970
How am I supposed to live without you?

136
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,800
I'm sorry for your loss.

137
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,090
I have a sister too. I know.

138
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:08,199
I understand.

139
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,439
Now that you're dead,

140
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,250
how am I supposed

141
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:14,160
to pay off my debts?

142
00:09:18,290 --> 00:09:19,730
My father wore

143
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,559
the heirloom every day.

144
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:22,649
He never took it off.

145
00:09:22,650 --> 00:09:23,400
How did it

146
00:09:23,410 --> 00:09:26,249
suddenly become a fake?

147
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,330
Calm down.

148
00:09:28,250 --> 00:09:29,330
Tell me.

149
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:32,129
After he passed it to your sister,
did she wear it every day?

150
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:33,280
She did.

151
00:09:33,930 --> 00:09:35,319
I cut it off her neck myself

152
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:35,929
while

153
00:09:35,930 --> 00:09:38,249
she was asleep.

154
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,559
If it was fake,

155
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:40,169
there's no way

156
00:09:40,170 --> 00:09:42,610
she wouldn't know.

157
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:46,799
Or maybe she knew all along
and wore it anyway so no one would find out.

158
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:47,970
Impossible.

159
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:50,529
It was an imperial gift
from the Qianlong Emperor.

160
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:52,640
It can't be fake.

161
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:55,520
Did your sister have any enemies?

162
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,610
The kind who wanted her dead?

163
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:02,959
(To Rid the People of Evil)

164
00:10:02,960 --> 00:10:06,000
Maybe my brother-in-law
had a grudge against her.

165
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,959
She wanted a divorce.
At worst, it would've hurt his pride.

166
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,529
Still,

167
00:10:10,530 --> 00:10:12,920
he wouldn't kill her over that.

168
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:16,160
He may be a bit sleazy,

169
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:19,049
but at least he has a respectable job.

170
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:20,439
Unlike Chang Fei.

171
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:22,079
That pretty boy

172
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,730
mooches off women.

173
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,409
You mentioned Chang Fei.

174
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:26,920
What do you think of him?

175
00:10:27,050 --> 00:10:28,370
Not good.

176
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:30,959
I just don't understand

177
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:31,599
what my sister

178
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,970
saw in him.

179
00:10:35,530 --> 00:10:36,929
She was a strong woman.

180
00:10:36,930 --> 00:10:39,610
What was she thinking?

181
00:10:55,370 --> 00:10:56,250
Who is it?

182
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,760
Wan'er?

183
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,280
What are you doing here?

184
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:02,850
Where's Yuan Hong?

185
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,610
He's working late at the station.

186
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:05,719
Here.

187
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,800
Try this tea.

188
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:10,730
You came to see me?

189
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:13,210
I was tired after tennis,
so I stopped by to rest.

190
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:16,169
You play in Anzhen.

191
00:11:16,170 --> 00:11:16,959
This is Chengnan.

192
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,310
You came all the way here to rest?

193
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:20,730
Have a good rest.

194
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,199
Looks like your injury is almost healed.

195
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,570
Why aren't you home yet?

196
00:11:28,170 --> 00:11:30,090
It's more convenient
for the investigation.

197
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:34,860
Yuan Hong thinks Chang Fei,
Ma Yuzhen's pretty boy, is suspicious.

198
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:35,900
He's out asking around now.

199
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:37,600
If there's news,
I need to head back to the station.

200
00:11:37,600 --> 00:11:38,520
Chang Fei?

201
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,719
You know him?

202
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:40,599
I do,

203
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,679
but we're not close.

204
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,400
He used to be my tennis partner.

205
00:11:43,530 --> 00:11:45,719
It's said he studied in America.

206
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,850
He came back from overseas

207
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,559
to be a tennis partner?

208
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:49,529
That happens.

209
00:11:49,530 --> 00:11:51,719
His family used to be wealthy,
but then fell on hard times.

210
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,769
Tennis is the only thing

211
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:53,920
he's good at.

212
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:55,959
But he's got sticky fingers.

213
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,889
He once stole a member's jewelry

214
00:11:57,890 --> 00:11:59,289
and hid it in his tennis basket.

215
00:11:59,290 --> 00:12:01,200
He claimed someone must've
left it there by mistake.

216
00:12:03,470 --> 00:12:06,230
(Changsheng Tennis Club)

217
00:12:19,530 --> 00:12:20,850
Where did you find them?

218
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:24,120
Chang Fei plays tennis every day

219
00:12:24,650 --> 00:12:26,289
and always carries a change of clothes,

220
00:12:26,290 --> 00:12:27,839
so carrying a big bag

221
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,719
and coming and going

222
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,160
wouldn't raise suspicions.

223
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,529
But we already searched

224
00:12:33,530 --> 00:12:34,800
his locker and Ma Yuzhen's.

225
00:12:35,010 --> 00:12:37,129
Wan'er told me the tennis club

226
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:38,129
gives every member

227
00:12:38,130 --> 00:12:39,559
a basket of practice balls.

228
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:40,439
Everyone

229
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:41,490
leaves them there,

230
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:43,529
with their name on the basket.

231
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,049
After each session,

232
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:46,309
the ball boys put them away

233
00:12:46,309 --> 00:12:47,950
(Changsheng Tennis Club)
in the storage room.

234
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:49,910
(Changsheng Tennis Club)

235
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,800
Only the ball boys
have access to that room.

236
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:03,049
Even if you searched the club,

237
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:04,280
you'd never think to look there.

238
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:07,280
Mr. Zhao,

239
00:13:08,530 --> 00:13:09,490
I'm so...

240
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:16,839
Mr. Zhao.

241
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,640
Thank you so much, Mr. Zhao.

242
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,289
The payout on this claim is enormous.

243
00:13:20,290 --> 00:13:21,839
At this morning's board meeting,

244
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,479
the shareholders
nearly flipped the table...

245
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,920
Wait.

246
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:27,599
There were only
33 newly made jade pieces.

247
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,439
Four antique jades are still missing.

248
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,490
Check them.

249
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:34,719
Mandarin duck round box.

250
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:35,839
Jade brush washer.

251
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,079
Lotus crown.

252
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,949
Twin phoenix pendant.

253
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:39,829
(Mandarin duck round box, Jade brush washer)

254
00:13:39,829 --> 00:13:41,920
(Lotus crown, Twin phoenix pendant)
These four ancient jades...

255
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:46,369
Why did those ancient jades go?

256
00:13:46,370 --> 00:13:48,040
You should ask her brother.

257
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,719
He squandered the family fortune.

258
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,320
In the past year alone, he racked up
debts of over a hundred thousand.

259
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:54,599
Yuzhen gave him four ancient jades

260
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,289
to pay them off.

261
00:13:56,290 --> 00:13:57,449
Mandarin duck round box.

262
00:13:57,450 --> 00:13:58,129
Jade brush washer.

263
00:13:58,130 --> 00:13:59,149
Lotus crown.

264
00:13:59,150 --> 00:14:00,169
Twin phoenix pendant.

265
00:14:00,170 --> 00:14:01,210
That's right.

266
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,959
But as far as we know,

267
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,599
no one in Beijing's antiques trade

268
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:07,160
saw them on the market.

269
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,889
His creditors were all Westerners.

270
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,850
They shipped them overseas directly.

271
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:12,529
The landlord now demands

272
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:14,719
ten years' rent upfront,

273
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:16,559
and we still owe the bank
for the raw jade.

274
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,199
We're really out of money.

275
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,049
So you staged the robbery yourselves

276
00:14:20,050 --> 00:14:22,330
to collect the insurance money.

277
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:30,880
Chang Fei,

278
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:32,779
if you don't tell us the truth,

279
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,730
Ma Yuzhen will have died for nothing.

280
00:14:35,130 --> 00:14:37,250
The killer is still at large.

281
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:43,970
Yes.

282
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:47,370
We planned it all in advance.

283
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,679
Fei.

284
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:02,009
Yuzhen,

285
00:15:02,010 --> 00:15:03,169
what happened?

286
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:03,999
(Changsheng Tennis Club)

287
00:15:03,999 --> 00:15:06,649
Shunzi just stole
the green jade inkstone.

288
00:15:06,650 --> 00:15:08,319
Seriously? Has he lost his mind?

289
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,319
Isn't that perfect?

290
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:11,160
Even heaven is helping us.

291
00:15:17,890 --> 00:15:18,839
Wrap it up.

292
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,640
I'll do it.

293
00:15:22,550 --> 00:15:24,470
(Changsheng Tennis Club)

294
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:29,850
Move.

295
00:15:34,050 --> 00:15:34,439
Yuzhen.

296
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,690
Why are you wrapping it in cloth?

297
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:38,280
Silly.

298
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,610
Careful.

299
00:15:43,170 --> 00:15:45,800
Shunzi is the only one
who uses this hammer.

300
00:15:46,010 --> 00:15:47,970
His fingerprints are all over it.

301
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:51,000
Call the police later.

302
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:53,199
Once they find the green jade inkstone

303
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,839
and match his fingerprints,

304
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:55,959
who'd believe

305
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:58,400
he didn't steal the rest?

306
00:15:59,050 --> 00:16:00,679
Once the theft is confirmed

307
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,079
and the items are declared missing,

308
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:04,760
the insurance company
will have to pay in full.

309
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:07,400
We thought

310
00:16:08,290 --> 00:16:10,210
the plan couldn't fail

311
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:12,649
with a perfect scapegoat.

312
00:16:12,650 --> 00:16:15,129
So I hid the stolen items
at the tennis club,

313
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:16,760
then called the police.

314
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:19,250
But I honestly didn't kill her.

315
00:16:21,890 --> 00:16:23,439
What are you doing?

316
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,079
Cooperate, and it'll go easier on you.

317
00:16:25,080 --> 00:16:26,120
Wait.

318
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:27,959
Why are you arresting me?

319
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,289
I didn't kill her.

320
00:16:29,290 --> 00:16:31,079
Insurance fraud, framing an innocent man.

321
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:31,799
Either charge

322
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,640
is enough to put you behind bars.

323
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,640
But...

324
00:16:39,940 --> 00:16:42,500
(The victim's ex-husband, Shi Litai.
The victim's husband, Chang Fei.)

325
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,990
(The victim's younger brother, Ma Buyan)

326
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:45,789
So far,

327
00:16:45,790 --> 00:16:47,730
none of them looks like a suspect.

328
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:50,959
Ma Buyan has no opportunity.

329
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,799
Chang Fei has no motive.

330
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,250
Shi Litai lacks the means.

331
00:16:59,550 --> 00:17:01,839
(Antique dealer, Miss Qiu)

332
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,559
Don't you think

333
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:04,250
Miss Qiu seems suspicious?

334
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:07,719
If Kobayashi believed
the blood jade was cursed,

335
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:08,959
why did he ask Zhang Baochen

336
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:11,450
to buy it at a high price six years ago?

337
00:17:13,170 --> 00:17:17,280
So the one who wanted the jade pendant
wasn't Kobayashi.

338
00:17:18,930 --> 00:17:21,479
During the Boxer Rebellion,
Master Ma fled west

339
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,999
with his family

340
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,199
and the imperial relatives,

341
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,679
eventually settling in Xi'an.

342
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:28,040
After taking a second wife,
he had a younger son.

343
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:29,649
It wasn't until the first year
of Emperor Xuantong's reign,

344
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:32,890
after Empress Dowager Cixi's funeral,
that the family moved back to Beijing.

345
00:17:34,810 --> 00:17:35,800
And?

346
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:41,600
Miss Qiu comes from Xi'an.

347
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:45,089
Everyone in the antiques trade knows
Master Ma lived in poverty

348
00:17:45,090 --> 00:17:46,519
while he was in Xi'an.

349
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:48,039
The house he lived in

350
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,730
belonged to his second wife.

351
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:51,329
So he wasn't wealthy

352
00:17:51,330 --> 00:17:52,690
back then.

353
00:17:52,690 --> 00:17:54,420
In the first year
of Emperor Xuantong's reign,

354
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:56,840
shortly after returning to Beijing,
he opened the jade shop.

355
00:17:57,570 --> 00:17:58,890
Something important

356
00:17:59,890 --> 00:18:00,949
must've happened in between.

357
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:04,070
(End of Episode 30)

358
00:18:05,441 --> 00:18:07,081
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

359
00:18:07,081 --> 00:18:08,621
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

360
00:18:08,621 --> 00:18:09,871
♪However, the world changes♪

361
00:18:09,871 --> 00:18:11,791
♪You'll still be by my side♪

362
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:13,481
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

363
00:18:13,481 --> 00:18:15,051
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

364
00:18:15,051 --> 00:18:16,621
♪If this is my final chapter♪

365
00:18:16,621 --> 00:18:19,121
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
